line_1: And Learn to what the Totall will amount;
line_2: Of happiest Love's Delights Sum up th' Account,

line_1: As tell them o'er, so great th' amount.
line_2: As well might I the sands recount,

line_1: OF all my experience how vast the amount,
line_2: Since fifteen long winters I fairly can count!

line_1: Shall find them rated at their full amount,
line_2: The good he scorn'd all carried to account.

line_1: Ask not, to what his Charities amount;
line_2: So many Myriads swell the vast Account.

line_1: Whose vast expences to such sums amount,
line_2: That the tax'd Gaul scarce furnish'd out th' account:

line_1: Your feelings in their full amount,
line_2: Are all upon your own account.

line_1: To what a mighty sum our ills amount,
line_2: And give a faithful, tho' a sad account.

line_1: And new — who knows to what amount?
Your sum of glory boasts a like amount;
line_2: In Reason's eye, in Wisdom's fair account,

line_1: And credit for the gross amount;
line_2: When Stewards pass a boot account,

line_1: But throw them in to vast amount;
line_2: Of sighs and groans take no account,
